{"title_page": "Antoni \u0141ukasiewicz", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Antoni \u0141ukasiewicz\n| image               = Antoni \u0141ukasiewicz.jpg\n| caption             = \n| fullname            = Antoni \u0141ukasiewicz\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1983|6|26|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Warsaw]], [[Poland]]\n| height              = {{convert|1.88|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}}\n| position            = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| currentclub         = [[Arka Gdynia]]\n| clubnumber          = 6\n| years1              = 2002\u20132006| clubs1 = [[Polonia Warsaw]] | caps1 = 80| goals1 = 0\n| years2              = 2006\u20132008| clubs2 = [[Elche CF|Elche]] | caps2 = 15| goals2 = 0\n| years3              = 2007\u20132008| clubs3 = \u2192 [[U.D. Leiria|Uni\u00e3o de Leiria]] (loan) | caps3 = 13| goals3 = 0\n| years4              = 2008\u20132012| clubs4 = [[\u015al\u0105sk Wroc\u0142aw]] | caps4 = 58| goals4 = 1\n| years5              = 2011     | clubs5 = \u2192 [[\u0141KS \u0141\u00f3d\u017a]] (loan)| caps5 = 12| goals5 = 3\n| years6              = 2012     | clubs6 = [[\u0141KS \u0141\u00f3d\u017a]] | caps6 = 11 | goals6 = 0\n| years7              = 2012\u20132014| clubs7 = [[G\u00f3rnik Zabrze]] | caps7 = 25 | goals7 = 0\n| years8              = 2014\u2013    | clubs8 = [[Arka Gdynia]] | caps8 = 98 | goals8 = 7\n| nationalyears1      = 2004\u20132005| nationalteam1 = [[Poland national under-21 football team|Poland U-21]] | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = \n| nationalyears2      = 2008\u20132009| nationalteam2 = [[Poland national football team|Poland]] | nationalcaps2 = 2| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| medaltemplates      = \n| club-update         = 18 August 2017\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n\n'''Antoni \u0141ukasiewicz''' (born 26 June 1983 in [[Warsaw]]) is a [[Poles|Polish]] footballer who plays as a [[Defender (football)|defender]] for [[Arka Gdynia]].\n\n==Career==\n\n===Club===\nIn August 2007, he was loaned to [[U.D. Leiria]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/newsid=573529.html|title=\u0141ukasiewicz loaned to Leiria|date=2007-08-21|accessdate=2010-04-12|publisher=UEFA.com}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2011, he was loaned to [[\u0141KS \u0141\u00f3d\u017a]] on a half-year deal<ref>[http://www.90minut.pl/news/166/news1667675-Antoni-Lukasiewicz-w-LKS-ie.html Antoni \u0141ukasiewicz w \u0141KS-ie] 30.08.2011, 90minut.pl</ref> and turned his loan into a permanent deal on 23 February 2012.\n\n===International===\n\u0141ukasiewicz debuted for [[Poland national football team|Poland]] in December 2008 against Serbia. He is a former captain of Poland's U-21 national team.\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Club===\n;Arka Gdynia\n* [[Polish Cup]]: [[2016\u201317 Polish Cup|2016\u201317]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{90minut|3883}}\n* {{NFT player|29761}}\n* {{soccerway|antoni-lukasiewicz/24622}}\n\n{{Arka Gdynia squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lukasiewicz, Antoni}}\n[[Category:Polish footballers]]\n[[Category:Polish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Poland international footballers]]\n[[Category:Polonia Warsaw players]]\n[[Category:\u015al\u0105sk Wroc\u0142aw players]]\n[[Category:\u0141KS \u0141\u00f3d\u017a players]]\n[[Category:Elche CF players]]\n[[Category:U.D. Leiria players]]\n[[Category:G\u00f3rnik Zabrze players]]\n[[Category:Arka Gdynia players]]\n[[Category:Primeira Liga players]]\n[[Category:Ekstraklasa players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Spain]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Polish expatriate sportspeople in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Warsaw]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n\n\n{{Poland-footy-defender-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Antoni \u0141ukasiewicz\n| image               = Antoni \u0141ukasiewicz.jpg\n| caption             = \n| fullname            = Antoni \u0141ukasiewicz\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1983|6|26|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Warsaw]], [[Poland]]\n| height              = {{convert|1.88|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}}\n| position            = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| currentclub         = [[Arka Gdynia]]\n| clubnumber          = 6\n| years1              = 2002\u20132006| clubs1 = [[Polonia Warsaw]] | caps1 = 80| goals1 = 0\n| years2              = 2006\u20132008| clubs2 = [[Elche CF|Elche]] | caps2 = 15| goals2 = 0\n| years3              = 2007\u20132008| clubs3 = \u2192 [[U.D. Leiria|Uni\u00e3o de Leiria]] (loan) | caps3 = 13| goals3 = 0\n| years4              = 2008\u20132012| clubs4 = [[\u015al\u0105sk Wroc\u0142aw]] | caps4 = 58| goals4 = 1\n| years5              = 2011     | clubs5 = \u2192 [[\u0141KS \u0141\u00f3d\u017a]] (loan)| caps5 = 12| goals5 = 3\n| years6              = 2012     | clubs6 = [[\u0141KS \u0141\u00f3d\u017a]] | caps6 = 11 | goals6 = 0\n| years7              = 2012\u20132014| clubs7 = [[G\u00f3rnik Zabrze]] | caps7 = 25 | goals7 = 0\n| years8              = 2014\u2013    | clubs8 = [[Arka Gdynia]] | caps8 = 98 | goals8 = 7\n| nationalyears1      = 2004\u20132005| nationalteam1 = [[Poland national under-21 football team|Poland U-21]] | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = \n| nationalyears2      = 2008\u20132009| nationalteam2 = [[Poland national football team|Poland]] | nationalcaps2 = 2| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| medaltemplates      = \n| club-update         = 18 August 2017\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n\n'''Antoni \u0141ukasiewicz''' (born 26 June 1983 in [[Warsaw]]) is a [[Poles|Polish]] footballer who plays as a [[Defender (football)|defender]] for [[Arka Gdynia]].\n\n==Career==\n\n===Club===\nIn August 2007, he was loaned to [[U.D. Leiria]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/newsid=573529.html|title=\u0141ukasiewicz loaned to Leiria|date=2007-08-21|accessdate=2010-04-12|publisher=UEFA.com}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2011, he was loaned to [[\u0141KS \u0141\u00f3d\u017a]] on a half-year deal<ref>[http://www.90minut.pl/news/166/news1667675-Antoni-Lukasiewicz-w-LKS-ie.html Antoni \u0141ukasiewicz w \u0141KS-ie] 30.08.2011, 90minut.pl</ref> and turned his loan into a permanent deal on 23 February 2012.\n\n===International===\n\u0141ukasiewicz debuted for [[Poland national football team|Poland]] in December 2008 against Serbia. He is a former captain of Poland's U-21 national team.\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Club===\n;Arka Gdynia\n* [[Polish Cup]]: [[2016\u201317 Polish Cup|2016\u201317]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{90minut|3883}}\n* {{NFT player|29761}}\n* {{soccerway|antoni-lukasiewicz/24622}}\n\n{{Arka Gdynia squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lukasiewicz, Antoni}}\n[[Category:Polish footballers]]\n[[Category:Polish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Poland international footballers]]\n[[Category:Polonia Warsaw players]]\n[[Category:\u015al\u0105sk Wroc\u0142aw players]]\n[[Category:\u0141KS \u0141\u00f3d\u017a players]]\n[[Category:Elche CF players]]\n[[Category:U.D. Leiria players]]\n[[Category:G\u00f3rnik Zabrze players]]\n[[Category:Arka Gdynia players]]\n[[Category:Primeira Liga players]]\n[[Category:Ekstraklasa players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Spain]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Polish expatriate sportspeople in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Warsaw]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n\n\n{{Poland-footy-defender-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Severo", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:AddingCategory:Footballers from Warsaw", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antoni_%C5%81ukasiewicz"}
